  <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
    <body>

        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="AN148.1-kilavi">pakalvaruvāṉai iravu <app><lem>varaveṉṟatu</lem><rdg wit="#C2 #3 #RK">varakeṉṟatu</rdg></app>.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">That which tells the one who came by day to come at night.</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
            <lg xml:id="AN148.1">
              <l>paṉaittira ḷaṉṉa <supplied>parē</supplied>reṟuḻt taṭakkaik</l>
              <l>kolaicciṉan tavirā mataṉuṭai muṉpiṉ</l>
              <l>vaṇṭupaṭu kaṭāat tuyarmarup piyāṉai</l>
              <l><supplied>ta</supplied>ṇkamaḻ cilampiṉ marampaṭat tolaicci</l>
              <l>yuṟupuli <supplied>yu</supplied>raṟa kutti vi<supplied>ṟa</supplied>lkaṭintu</l>
              <l>ciṟutiṉaip perumpuṉam vavvu nāṭa</l>
              <l>kaṭumparik kutirai yāa yeyiṉa</l>
              <l>ṉeṭuntēr miñiliyoṭu porutukaḷam paṭṭeṉak</l>
              <l>kāṇiya <supplied>ce</supplied>llāk kūkai nāṇik</l>
              <l>kaṭumpakal vaḻaṅkā tā<supplied>a</supplied>ṅ kiṭumpai</l>
              <l>peritā lamma vivaṭkē yataṉā<supplied>ṉ</supplied></l>
              <l>mālai varutal vēṇṭuñ cōlai</l>
              <l>muḷaimēy peruṅkaḷiṟu vaḻaṅku</l>
              <l>malaimuta laṭukkatta ciṟukā lāṟē.</l>
            </lg>
            <lg xml:lang="en">
                <l rend="indent8">O man from a land, (6d)</l>
                <l>where the elephant with high tusks [and temple] vents swarmed by bees, (3)</l>
                <l>of rut[-induced] strength that is not restrained in [his] murderous anger, (2)</l>
                <l>with a broad trunk huge, beautiful [and] mighty like the round of a Palmyra tree, (1)</l>
                <l>wrecks havoc, for trees to fall, on the cool fragrant mountain side, (4)</l>
                <l>goring the suffering tiger so that it roars [and] victoriously chasing it away, (5)</l>
                <l>[then] snatching the little millet from the big field, (6a-c)</l>
                <l>big, alas, is the distress of her (10d-11c)</l>
                <l>in that place where the owl does not roam by fierce midday,</l>
                <l>ashamed that it cannot see, (9-10c)</l>
                <l>because on the battlefield, after fighting with Miñili with long chariot,</l>
                <l>the hunter Āay has fallen, with swift-gaited horses. (7f.)</l>
                <l rend="indent8">Therefore, (11d)</l>
                <l>coming in the evening is necessary, (12a-c)</l>
                <l>on the path with little [side-]tracks from the side by the base of the mountain, (14)</l>
                <l>where the big elephant bull roams, grazing on sprouts in the grove. (12df.)</l>
            </lg>
        </div>
    </body>
  </text>
